BriefDescription: Count all other hardware assists or traps that are not necessarily architecturally exposed (through a software handler) beyond FP; SSE-AVX mix and A/D assists who are counted by dedicated sub-events.
PublicDescription: Count all other hardware assists or traps that are not necessarily architecturally exposed (through a software handler) beyond FP; SSE-AVX mix and A/D assists who are counted by dedicated sub-events.  This includes, but not limited to, assists at EXE or MEM uop writeback like AVX* load/store/gather/scatter (non-FP GSSE-assist ) , assists generated by ROB like PEBS and RTIT, Uncore trap, RAR (Remote Action Request) and CET (Control flow Enforcement Technology) assists.

BriefDescription: ASSISTS.PAGE_FAULT
Counts cycles where the pipeline is stalled due to serializing operations.
Counts the number of unhalted cycles a Core is blocked due to a lock In Progress issued by another core
PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles a Core is blocked due to a lock In Progress issued by another core. Counts on a per core basis.

BriefDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles a Core is blocked due to an Accepted lock it issued, includes both split and non-split lock cycles.
PublicDescription: Counts the number of unhalted cycles a Core is blocked due to an Accepted lock it issued, includes both split and non-split lock cycles. Counts on a per core basis.

BriefDescription: Counts the number of non-split locks such as UC locks issued by a Core (does not include cache locks)
Counts the number of split locks issued by a Core
Count number of times a load is depending on another load that had just write back its data or in previous or  2 cycles back. This event supports in-direct dependency through a single uop.
Counts the number of cycles the L2 Prefetchers are at throttle level 0
Counts the number of cycles the L2 Prefetcher throttle level is at 1
Counts the number of cycles the L2 Prefetcher throttle level is at 2
Counts the number of cycles the L2 Prefetcher throttle level is at 3
Counts the number of cycles the L2 Prefetcher throttle level is at 4
Counts the number of uops executed on all Integer ports.
Counts the number of uops executed on a load port.
PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on a load port.  This event counts for integer uops even if the destination is FP/vector

BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 0.
Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 1.
Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 2.
Counts the number of uops executed on integer port 3.
Counts the number of uops executed on integer port  0,1, 2, 3.
Counts the number of uops executed on a Store address port.
PublicDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on a Store address port. This event counts integer uops even if the data source is FP/vector

BriefDescription: Counts the number of uops executed on an integer store data and jump port.

Counts the number of LLC prefetches that were  throttled due to Dynamic Prefetch Throttling.  The throttle requestor/source could be from the uncore/SOC or the Dead Block Predictor. Counts on a per core basis.
Counts the number of LLC prefetches throttled due to Demand Throttle Prefetcher.  DTP Global Triggered with no Local Override. Counts on a per core basis.
Counts the number of LLC prefetches not throttled by DTP due to local override.  These prefetches may still be throttled due to another throttler mechanism. Counts on a per core basis.
Counts the number of LLC prefetches throttled due to LLC hit rate in <insert knob name here>. Counts on a per core basis.
Counts the number of LLC prefetches throttled due to exceeding the XQ threshold set by either XQ_THRESOLD_DTP or LLC_XQ_THRESHOLD. Counts on a per core basis.
Counts cycles where no execution is happening due to loads waiting for L1 cache (that is: no execution & load in flight & no load missed L1 cache)
Counts cycles where no execution is happening due to loads waiting for L2 cache (that is: no execution & load in flight & load missed L1 & no load missed L2 cache)
Counts cycles where no execution is happening due to loads waiting for L3 cache (that is: no execution & load in flight & load missed L1 & load missed L2 cache & no load missed L3 Cache)
Counts cycles where no execution is happening due to loads waiting for Memory (that is: no execution & load in flight & a load missed L3 cache)
Counts all requests that have any type of response.
Counts writebacks of modified cachelines that have any type of response.
Counts writebacks of non-modified cachelines that have any type of response.
Counts demand instruction fetches and L1 instruction cache prefetches that have any type of response.
Counts demand instruction fetches and L1 instruction cache prefetches that were supplied by DRAM.
Counts demand data reads that have any type of response.
Counts demand data reads that have any type of response.
Counts demand data reads that were supplied by DRAM.
Counts demand data reads that were supplied by DRAM.
Counts demand read for ownership (RFO) requests and software prefetches for exclusive ownership (PREFETCHW) that have any type of response.
Counts demand read for ownership (RFO) requests and software prefetches for exclusive ownership (PREFETCHW) that have any type of response.
Counts demand read for ownership (RFO) requests and software prefetches for exclusive ownership (PREFETCHW) that were supplied by DRAM.
Counts full streaming stores (64 bytes, WCiLF) that have any type of response.
Counts partial streaming stores (less than 64 bytes, WCiL) that have any type of response.
Counts streaming stores that have any type of response.
Counts streaming stores that have any type of response.
Cycles when Reservation Station (RS) is empty for the thread.
PublicDescription: Counts cycles during which the reservation station (RS) is empty for this logical processor. This is usually caused when the front-end pipeline runs into starvation periods (e.g. branch mispredictions or i-cache misses)

BriefDescription: Counts end of periods where the Reservation Station (RS) was empty.
PublicDescription: Counts end of periods where the Reservation Station (RS) was empty. Could be useful to closely sample on front-end latency issues (see the FRONTEND_RETIRED event of designated precise events)

BriefDescription: Cycles when RS was empty and a resource allocation stall is asserted
Counts the number of issue slots in a UMWAIT or TPAUSE instruction where no uop issues due to the instruction putting the CPU into the C0.1 activity state.
Counts the number issue slots not consumed  due to a  color request for an FCW or MXCSR control register when all 4 colors (copies) are already in use
Cycles the uncore cannot take further requests
PublicDescription: number of cycles when the thread is active and the uncore cannot take any further requests (for example prefetches, loads or stores initiated by the Core that miss the L2 cache).

BriefDescription: Counts the number of prefetch requests that were promoted in the XQ to a demand request.
Counts the number of prefetch requests that were promoted in the XQ to a demand code read.
Counts the number of prefetch requests that were promoted in the XQ to a demand read.
Counts the number of prefetch requests that were promoted in the XQ to a demand RFO.
